Guns are the stuff of stories now. Legends of great blasts and speeding bullets are recounted to new generations. They are but one of the few luxuries of the old world. Zyra-a young girl of twelve, cunning and vicious-must contend with her entrapment by a brutal clan, known as The Skoners, in the western territory. Only through ingenuity and a reluctant alliance with a dissenting member of her enemy can she hope to survive. Yet all is not what it seems. Within the ranks of The Skoners, the scent of mutiny permeates the air when Tank-an animalistic killer, bent on achieving honor through blood-moves to overthrow the current leadership run by the wise and calculated Gauge, and undermine years of Gauge's endeavors to implement a new society in the western territory, where all can ride hard and live free.

title: I Luv Barcelona
des: An amazing journey in the beautiful and charming city of Barcelona where I admired the Sagrada Familia, Casa Mila, and Casa Batllo the impressible work of the famous Catalan architect Antoni Gaudi. The Castle of Montjuic was one of my favorites places to visit it has an incredible view of the city of Barcelona. I enjoyed very much Barceloneta beach and the Vell Pier, I loved my walks to El born neighborhood and the Ramblas where I enjoyed a delicious Paella with my friend Thais. I was so fortunate to visit Barcelona during the very well attended Feria of Santa Lucia where you can feel the Christmas spirit everywhere. The Gothic Quarter is my favorite place to visit; it has many restaurants, bars, and clubs, the stand-up-comedy at Craft Barcelona was so much fun, the tapas is absolutely fantastic, moreover, in the Gothic quarter you can find the incredible Barcelona Cathedral, the City Hall, many plazas and charming and medieval streets, finally, Ciutadella park, the Boqueria market, the Catalunya plaza, the Palace of Catalan Music are places that are a must to visit.
